We discovered that our instance was effectively unusable because the index became corrupt but the doHealthCheck was reporting the instance as in good condition.

Because a broken index does really put a JIRA instance down this must be included in the health check.

It seems that with 6.3 the index corruption became again a reality, reminding us of JIRA 3.x index instability.

